{"type":null,"faqId":37991,"title":"How do I adjust the photo size","answer":"<style type=\"text/css\">.b1{white-space-collapsing:preserve;}\r\n.d1{margin: 1.18125in 0.7875in 1.18125in 0.7875in;}\r\n.p1{margin-left:1.18125in;margin-top:0.11111111in;margin-bottom:0.11111111in;text-align:start;hyphenate:auto;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;}\r\n.s1{font-weight:bold;}\r\n</style>\n<div>\n<p><span>The photo size depends on the camera resolution. The higher the resolution, the larger the photo.</span> </p>\n<p><a name=\"ZH-CN_TOPIC_0005891058\"></a><span>For EMUI 2.0 and EMUI 2.3, enter the camera viewfinder mode and select </span><img style=\"WIDTH: 0.305in; HEIGHT: 0.223in; VERTICAL-ALIGN: text-bottom\" src=\"http://consumer.huawei.com/support/servlet/imageServlet?dlType=HtmlAreaImage&imageId=123141\"><span>. Select the </span><span class=\"s1\">Camera</span><span> tab and then select </span><span class=\"s1\">Resolution</span><span> to adjust the camera resolution.</span> </p>\n<p><span>For EMUI 3.0, enter the camera viewfinder mode and select </span><img style=\"WIDTH: 0.207in; HEIGHT: 0.145in; VERTICAL-ALIGN: text-bottom\" src=\"http://consumer.huawei.com/support/servlet/imageServlet?dlType=HtmlAreaImage&imageId=123142\"><span>. Then select </span><span class=\"s1\">Settings &gt; Resolution</span><span> to adjust the camera resolution.</span> </p>\n<p><span>The size of a photo can also be changed by opening the photo using </span><span class=\"s1\">Gallery</span><span> or another third-party app and cropping the image.</span> </p>\n</div>","faqTypeId":null,"faqType":null,"useful":0,"unUseful":0,"languageId":281,"languageName":"fa","faqCode":"3211","faqTypeCode":null,"isTop":"0","moduleCode":"faq","productId":null,"productCode":null,"postDate":1441091728000,"seriesProductName":"ALE-L21,CherryPlus-L11,CHM-U01,EDGE-U00,G510-0010,G510-0200,G525-U00,G610-U00,G610-U20,G615-U10,G630-U10,G630-U20,G6-U10,G700-U10,G730-U10,G750-U10,G760-L01,GRA-L03,H30-U10,H60-L04,